{
  "stem": "13469.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we really enjoyed ourselves in Holland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The interesting thing is-- although at the time we didn't realize it-- is that we didn't have any Jewish friends at all.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We, again, seemed to live a very secular life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I, I don't remember ever having gone to a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I don't remember any Friday nights and, and all those sort of things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "As it happened, there, there was a Jewish family living next to us and another Jewish family living opposite us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But I still believe that there weren't many Jews [LAUGHS] in Heemstede in that area.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I may well have been wrong.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It's interesting that the family that lived opposite us in that street, in Johannes Vermeerstraat in Heemstede, were later on with us in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they were one of the very few families that got out of Belsen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They were exchanged.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they went to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we've heard of them after the war, you know, that they actually did get to Palestine and then lived there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think our parents must have told them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, we obviously knew that we were Jewish because, well, we were refugees from Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And therefore, I would imagine that both those families also were refugees from Germany because their name-- Mainz was the one, and Dietz was the other one.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mainz certainly is a very Germanic name, almost the same as Oppenheimer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, Mainz is very near to Oppenheimer in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I, I, I think, by the name, we probably deduced it wasn't a very Dutch name.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maybe, or maybe my parents told us that they were Jewish like us, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And maybe-- you're right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe we did know more about Judaism, and we did do more Judaism than I can remember.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
